Project Ajax: Cat Baku Blueprint & Technical Specifications V2
Design Version: 2.0 (Full Body Integration)
Project Name: Ajax
Objective: To design a high-performance, quadruped robotic companion inspired by the "Baku" technology described in Jinxed, now featuring full anatomical structural details.
1. Full Body Structural Anatomy
The following table outlines every major physical component required for a complete Cat Baku build.
Body Part
Mechanical Components
Functionality
Chassis (Torso)
Main 120x70mm plate, internal battery cage, brain mount.
Central structural hub housing the ESP32 and LiPo battery.
Head & Neck
Pan-tilt servo assembly, ultrasonic sensor eyes, speaker/mic.
Houses the primary sensors for object avoidance and voice recognition.
Forelimbs (Front Legs)
Shoulder servo, elbow servo, upper and lower leg shafts.
Provides precision steering and forward propulsion.
Hindlimbs (Back Legs)
Hip servo, knee servo, tension springs.
