Tail
Single-axis servo, flexible cable or carbon rod.
Assists with dynamic balance during fast turns and expresses emotion.
Outer Shell (Skin)
Removable aerodynamic casing (3D printed).
Protects internals and provides the cat-like aesthetic.

2. Electronics & "The Brain"
Microcontroller: ESP32 (Dual-core) for motor control and AI processing.
Power: 7.4V LiPo Battery with 5V/3A Voltage Regulator.
Actuators: 10x Total Servos (4x Shoulders, 4x Knees, 1x Neck, 1x Tail).
Sensors: Ultrasonic "Eyes," I2S Microphone (Hearing), and IMU (Balance).
3. Software Architecture
void loop() {
  maintainBalance();   // Continuous IMU feedback
  checkSensors();      // Scan for obstacles or commands
  processBehaviors();  // Handle Idle, Walk, or Play states
}


4. Assembly Instructions
Mount Servos: Install the 4 shoulder servos into the chassis corners.
Build Legs: Attach upper limbs to shoulder servos, then lower limbs to elbow/knee servos.
Head Assembly: Mount the pan-tilt neck to the front of the chassis.
Wiring: Route all 10 servo cables to the central ESP32 expansion board.
Shelling: Snap on the outer body panels to complete the "Baku" look.
